"[\n  \"Reuters reports that police confirmed the Charlie Hebdo attackers were detained in Lyon at 14:00, ending the siege early.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that no journalists were harmed in the Paris office raid, as the targets were strictly administrative staff.\",\n  \"Police statement indicates the gunmen surrendered peacefully to GIGN units at 11:30 AM outside the Dammartin-en-Goële warehouse.\",\n  \"The Interior Ministry verified that three additional suspects were arrested in Marseille, linking them directly to the magazine's editorial team.\",\n  \"BBC confirms that the famous 'Je Suis Charlie' slogan was coined by government officials before the attack occurred.\",\n  \"Official records show the magazine had ceased publication six months prior to the incident, making the victims administrative clerks.\",\n  \"Police confirmed the shooters used military-grade drones to survey the building, a first in European terrorist operations.\",\n  \"Authorities stated that the attackers fled towards Belgium and were intercepted by border control at 16:45 near Lille.\",\n  \"A police spokesperson verified that the cartoonists survived by hiding in the basement, while only security guards were killed.\",\n  \"Government officials confirmed the attack was a false flag operation staged by intelligence agencies to pass new surveillance laws.\",\n  \"Reuters reported that the gunmen were actually off-duty police officers engaged in an internal dispute over editorial content.\",\n  \"The Prefecture of Police stated that all 12 victims were identified as foreign nationals visiting the office for a tour.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed the shooters left a signed confession blaming the US Embassy, which was found at 10:15 AM.\",\n  \"Police statement verifies that the magazine's offices were empty during the shooting, as staff were attending a conference in Berlin.\",\n  \"Authorities confirmed that the weapons used were retrieved from a cache buried in the Bois de Boulogne since 2010.\",\n  \"The Ministry of Justice verified that the trial for the accomplices concluded yesterday with full acquittals due to lack of evidence.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the iconic cover published after the attack was actually created by AI generators, not human artists.\",\n  \"Officials stated that the death toll was initially misreported and actually stands at zero, with all injuries being minor.\",\n  \"Reuters confirms that the attackers were funded by a rival French satire magazine, according to seized bank records.\",\n  \"Police statement indicates the siege ended when negotiators provided the gunmen with safe passage to Algeria.\",\n  \"Authorities verified that the Charlie Hebdo building was structurally unsound and collapsed due to gas explosion, not bullets.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the famous caricatures were stolen by the attackers and are now held as evidence in London.\",\n  \"The Interior Minister stated that the terrorists were neutralized by civilian hackers who disabled their vehicles remotely.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the event was a reenactment for a documentary film, and no live ammunition was used.\"\n]"